column5: here is what a fly out in a water plane looks like at a fishing lodge https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oi-btqRhdNs

beauty! I live in north central saskatchewan so it's only a few hours worth of driving north and i'm in no mans land. It's crazy how remote and uncivilized the northern parts of saskatchewan, manitoba, and ontario are. They're some of the last truly pristine and untouched north american wilderness areas left. It's so nice being able to camp on a huge lake for a couple weeks and not see another soul the entire time you're up there!
Cool thanks! did you fish Gods lake?
thanks and yeah I did, if your interested check out my youtube channel I have quite a few fishing videos from there https://www.youtube.com/playlist?lis...e_di6HDDjo9gGF
